{
  "texts": [
    "As it is shown in Fig. 3, the input essay is represented using a convolutional recurrent neural network, which produces context vectors and sentence similarity vectors.",
    "The context vectors represent the semantic features of the essay, while the sentence similarity vectors reflect the coherence within the essay.",
    "Furthermore, this study incorporates rating criteria information by introducing sample essays.",
    "The rating criteria within the essays (cross-feature) are captured through contrastive learning between the input essay and the samples.",
    "The cross-feature details are conveyed through distance information extracted from the input and sample essays."
  ]
}